Date:  0/0/1951
Source:  Early Canterbury Runs
Author:  ACLAND
Vol / Page:  366
Edition:
Quote:  burnt chops: an expression somewhat akin to the expression 'burnt spur' which denoted the business of a high country mustering: 'So-and-so has taken to the b.s.', meaning he has taken on mustering.
